      • getSublists

        public static <T> java.util.List<java.util.List<T>> getSublists(java.util.List<T> list,
                                                                int subListSize)
                                                         throws java.lang.Exception
        Given a list, generate all possible sublists of the specified size. The generator maintains the order of the original list, no elements are duplicated. If n is the number of elements in the original list, the number of sublists of length k is n!/((n-k)!*k!). The sublists are build by choosing an element from the element following the current element.
        Type Parameters:
        T - type of list elements
        Parameters:
        list - the original list from which to compute the sublists
        subListSize - the size of the sublists
        Returns:
        list of sublists
        Throws:
        java.lang.Exception - when trying to create sublists that contain more elements than the original list

      • getAllSublists

        public static <T> java.util.List<java.util.List<T>> getAllSublists(java.util.List<T> list)
        Generate all sublists of the provided list. The original order is maintained. The number of generated sublists is Sum(k=1..n) n!/((n-k)!*k!).
        Type Parameters:
        T - type of list elements
        Parameters:
        list - the original list
        Returns:
        the list of all sublists
